fields.title: India says no plan to impose retaliatory tariffs on US goods
fields.text:
ndia does not plan to impose retaliatory tariffs on US goods after US President Donald Trump said he intends to end India's preferential trade treatment, a top trade official said
Commerce secretary Anup Wadhawan said the withdrawal of the Generalised System of Preferences (GSP) for Indian products would have limited impact

fields.title: Pulwama
fields.text:
Srinagar: 

An encounter broke out in Jammu and Kashmir's Pulwama between security forces and terrorists this morning. Two terrorist were killed in ongoing operation.

Police had information about the presence of two terrorists hiding in a house in Pulwama's Tral.

The target house has been razed to ground.

Mobile internet services have been suspended in the town

It was in Pulwama that over 40 CRPF soldiers were killed in a terror attack on February 14. Pakistan-based terror group Jaish-e-Mohammed claimed responsibility for the attack. Following this, Indian fighter jets destroyed Jaish's biggest training camp in Pakistan's Balakot.
